 NIGERIA’S talent hunt competition platform for indigenous budding Fuji artist, Ariya Repete has listed Sound Sultan, ID Cabasa and Puffy T as judges for this year’s edition tagged ‘Omoluabi Special’. Sound Sultan becomes the top judge while VJ Adams will be the host of the show. Ariya Repete ‘Omoluabi Special’, the eighth edition of the music competition, will celebrate amazing indigenous talents from southwestern Nigeria. This year’s edition will engage Nigerian A-list stars and Goldberg ambassadors, Olamide and Odunlade Adekola. Also, the organizers have decided to add a twist to this year’s edition by allowing fans to join in the elimination of contestants every week. This year, a total cash prize of N3million is up for grabs. Ariya Repete TV broadcast will commence from November 22, 2020, with exciting episodes to be aired every Sunday at 8 pm on Soundcity TV and ONTV. Speaking on the new edition, the Portfolio Manager, Mainstream Brands, Omotunde Adenusi said, ”Ariya Repete is a very special platform that allows us to showcase and celebrate the very best talents in Nigeria. Over the years, we have been able to delight our consumers with this initiative as well as provide some unforgettable memories for a lot of winners and viewers of past editions. We hope to make this edition filled with even more enjoyment”.